{"author":{"id":"cff9ab1d2ee9741039b2a60d90cca378a5320ba753398f6f3df8d03abcebee1b"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1771154857,"nonce":"4mEfgIL1Wjbt97ak/2ekNoAxnVg=","title":"Move Docker infrastructure files into docker/ subdirectory","message":"Docker Compose and Foreman both read .env from their working directory. Since the project root is volume-mounted into the container at /app, any .env meant for Docker Compose gets picked up by Foreman, causing env var conflicts (e.g., empty SECRET_KEY_BASE overriding the value from docker-compose.override.yml).\n\nFix: move all Docker infrastructure files (Dockerfile, docker-compose.yml, docker-compose.override.yml, docker-entrypoint.sh, Caddyfile, .env.example) into a docker/ subdirectory. Docker Compose reads .env relative to the compose file location, so docker/.env stays invisible to Foreman.\n\nPlan: docs/plans/docker-directory-restructure.md\n\nOpen decisions before implementation:\n- Entrypoint location: move to docker/ with explicit COPY in Dockerfile (recommended) vs keep in root\n- Convenience wrapper: bin/dc script (recommended) vs COMPOSE_FILE env var vs always cd docker/","files":null}]}